This is a breakfloor based map. You shoot down to break the blocks.

At the very bottom is a bomb site. Whichever terrorist has the bomb shoots down and plants the bomb. The bomb site is around a picture on the ground. The bottom has some scattered blocks down there and four blocks in the corner to help you get back up. Also use those scattered blocks to get up!

There are 16 spawn points in each spawn. Recommended/Maximum Players is 32.

Screen shot A is the two spawns with different colors.

Screen shot B is the bottom where the bomb site is.

*****

_sText: This is the same breakfloor all you breakfloorians like but modified by me. I added of course a jail hence the name breakfloor_jail. So when you fall down by some idiot teammate or by an enemy you won't die at the bottom, rather you teleport to jail. At each spawn point there is a surf sign on the walls. Shoot down the floor and the last glass block is where you can exit the enclosed breakfloor and surf down to the jail to open the jail door if a teammate is stuck in there. Even if you don't need to free a teammate there are blocks on the way with shotguns and smoke grenades on either side. On top of jail which is sort of hard to get to is where the snipers and semi-auto snipers are. In that same spot there are 3 teleport doors to get to either CT base T base or TOP. But since the floors might be broken when you teleport to the CT or T base you spawn on top of the light so you don't die.(water wouldn't work there) Also at the jail you can shoot and see through it from the outside but people inside it cannot. When you teleport back to the top middle wall I made it a bit wider only on the top part and put some weapons along with HEgrenades. There is also two ladders on both sides of the top middle divider because if you jump from there your health gets lowered, and like I said before water cannot work there. I also put a ladder at the top of the jail where the snipers are going down so that you don't die when you fall. I know it looks pretty pointless because people can just jump into the water at either side outside of the jail but it is an alternative. Another thing I added is another ramp by the jail that makes people surf into a wall that trigger teleports all the way to the top of the map. Yes I added a ceiling at the top, made of unbreakable glass that you can also shoot through from both sides. I placed a few weapons up there along with a couple flashgrenades. And to get down from there you just start walking towards the opening and it will boost you forward to get back to the ramps.

This map was mostly inspired by Supa’s work.  I had the idea of making a more breakable map independently, but soon discovered that I wasn’t the only one with that idea.  I ended up spending a lot of time at buildingblockscs.com’s servers (now defunct), where Supa’s maps were featured and where he was the resident mapper.  This release was the latest version of my previous break-map attempts, taking the hex-block idea from Supa’s works.  The hex-block is the perfect shape and size to maximize the potential breakable area of a Source-based map.

###########

Break 'n' Run 2

###########

Okay, This is a new style of gameplay for CSS (i think anyway)... i thought of the idea a few days ago, so this is my first attempt...

The idea is Left For Dead style CO-OP, but on a smaller scale, and not with zombies, with CT's...with guns lol. (so nothing like left for dead really...)

NOW THE IMPORTANT STUFF - PLEASE READ!!

*There are 4 T spawns and 12 CT's (so 4 player co-op)
*It was designed around having bots (very hard) as the CT's
*CT's start armed to the teeth, whilst the T's have a 10 second head start to go and find some guns/hide/run away/whatever...

HOW TO PLAY - READ THIS TOO! :) 

*Find a couple of mates (not very fun alone)
*Join T side - you will start with a pane of glass in front of you - THIS IS THE TRIGGER TO START THE GAME
*The glass has 200 HP - once its broken, you have 10 seconds to run into the room ahead and find some guns! 
*After 10 seconds, the wall holding back the CT's will break, and being bots (which they should be) will come and hunt you down! :)


There are various weapons/grenades located around the map, also a variety of routes to take for both teams.

QUESTIONS/COMMENTS/IDEAS all welcome! 

LET ME KNOW WHAT YOU THINK OF THE GAMEPLAY TYPE - il make some more maps for it if people want them :) 


Cheers! 


Gavin
